screen_desc: This screenshot shows the Google Messages app offering a prompt to activate chat features. It explains that users can chat over Wi-Fi and data, share higher quality photos, and more with others who have chat features. To enable this, the user must agree to the Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. There are two options: agreeing to activate chat features or using Messages without them. The user can click "Agree" to proceed.
